  Khap,a contemporary tale of traditional     
  massacre opens in the capital where two     
  youths Ria and Kush fall in love.           
  Meanwhile news channels highlight the       
  death of Veer and Surili,who are found      
  dead in Omkar Chaudhary's village.Ria       
  has no idea that Omkar is her grandfather.  
  Madhur, Ria's father,had left his native    
  village due to differences with Omkar over  
  the ruthless pratha of honour killings,     
  Madhur is chosen to lead a commission to    
  investigate the suspicious deaths of young  
  Veer and surili. Torn between his love for  
  his son and his strong belief in the pratha,
  Omkar promises Madhur that he would put an  
  end to these ruthless killings.             



